cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on video codec comparison and quality analysis, which falls under the multimedia domain. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses the application of a no-reference metric to video quality analysis, which involves computer vision techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper mentions the impact of compression on detailed textures and the blurring effect, which relates to information theory. 
- cs.MM (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an averaging technique to improve metric quality scores, which involves machine learning. 
- cs.MM (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the limitations of the metric and its inability to be used for video codec comparisons, which relates to human-computer interaction.
